edu.jhu.cs.oose.fall2011.cartagena.iface
Class Location

java.lang.Object
  edu.jhu.cs.oose.fall2011.cartagena.iface.Location

public class Location
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a location in a game of Cartagena. This class represents a Cartagena location as a value between 0 and 36 (inclusive). 0 represents the initial space for all pieces; the values between 1 and 36 each represent a space on the Cartagena board. This class is used to add meaning to the integers (since an object of this type is clearly a Cartagena location and not another kind of integer data) as well as to prevent mistakes in value ranges (since the constructor will reject invalid data immediately).
